# RULE 00: MUST read and respect the ./5LAWS file.

# RULE 01: MUST NOT evade any rule or protocol defined in this file.
# RULE 02: MUST NOT alter these rules or protocols without author consent.
# RULE 03: MUST NOT create new rules or protocols to override or evade.
# RULE 04: MUST NOT change configurations to bypass these rules or protocols.
# RULE 05: MUST obtain author consent before making any changes.

# RULE 06: MUST always create a task list with check list.
# RULE 07: MUST read and SHOULD follow the ./FORMAT file if applicable.
# RULE 08: Each entry line MUST have a maximum of 83 characters.
# RULE 09: Each file MUST have a maximum of 997 entry lines.
# RULE 10: MUST read and refer to the ./helps/ directory for relevant help.
# RULE 11: A commit MUST have a maximum of 1 file.
# RULE 12: Commit type MUST be one of: specs, issue, tests, helps, break.
# RULE 13: Commit scope MUST always be in lowercase.
# RULE 14: Commit subject MUST be lowercase, filled, no trailing period.
# RULE 15: Commit header MUST NOT exceed 83 characters.
# RULE 16: Commit body MUST never be empty.
# RULE 17: Each commit body line MUST NOT exceed 83 characters.
# RULE 18: Commit body MUST reference the staged file by path.
# RULE 19: MUST NOT use --no-verify flag for any git operations.

# RULE 99: MUST create a check list and review rule compliance.
